===Etymology===
From the {{etyl|de}} trademark {{term|Aspirin|lang=de}}, from {{term|Acetylirte Spirsäure||acetylated spiræic acid|lang=de}}. The trade name ''Aspirin'' is a registered trademark in some countries, but has entered the English language in generic usage.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|aspirins|-}}

# {{uncountable|pharmaceutical drug}} An [[analgesic]] [[drug]], [[acetylsalicylic acid]].
# {{countable}} A [[tablet]] containing this substance.

